Class TemplateVariantNotFoundException

  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    Serializable

    public class TemplateVariantNotFoundException
extends VariantResolutionException
    Specialized exception that is thrown when the variant can be handled by Ogham through a VariantResolver but the ResolvedPath provided by the VariantResolver points to an non-existing template.

    This exception provides the list of tested paths (the possible template paths for the variant) that seem to not exist. For example, using FreeMarker template engine, an HTML variant template referenced by "templates/register" may be located at either "templates/register.html.ftl" or "template/register.html.ftlh".
